title: Lakanal House Tower Block Fire
description:
The Lakanal House Tower Block Fire was a fire that occurred on 3rd July 2009 in Camberwell, London. Six people were killed and at least 20 people were injured when a fire developed and spread through a number of flats in a Lakanal House, a twelve storey tower block.

At 16:20 BST (15:20 UTC) on 3rd July 2009, a fire broke out in one of the flats of Lakanal House. London Fire Brigade responded with a total of eighteen fire engines attending the incident. The seat of the fire is thought to have been in a flat on the ninth floor.

London Fire Brigade rescued a number of people from the flats. The injured were taken to Guy's Hospital, King's College Hospital and Lewisham. One person admitted to Guys Hospital and two people admitted to King's College Hospital later died, as well as three people who died in the fire. Nine other people were treated at an emergency centre set up by Southwark Council. One of the firemen was also admitted to hospital after being injured while fighting the fire.
